olive oil
2 potato
1 carrot
1 tomato
1 cucumber
1 packet Halloumi
1 sachet Lemon Pepper Seasoning
1 tsp honey
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet chicken breast

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato and carrot into fries.
• Place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop tomato. Slice cucumber into half-moons.
• Cut halloumi into 1cm slices.
• Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.
• In a medium bowl, combine halloumi, lemon pepper spice blend, a pinch of salt and a drizzle of olive oil. Set aside.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook halloumi until golden brown, 1-2 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, add the honey and gently turn halloumi to coat. Transfer to a plate.
• Wash and dry the frying pan, then return to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

• In a large bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, tomato, cucumber, a pinch of salt and pepper and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Sprinkle with diced chicken. Season.
• Divide veggie fries, tomato salad and glazed lemon pepper halloumi between plates.
• Serve with Greek-style yoghurt. Enjoy!